\b Unix Raw Mode
\b0  - This is normally unchecked.\
If you get a login message from the host but cannot type anything, uncheck this option. If you get double characters when you type, check this option.\
\
Checking Unix Raw mode may keep the connection from closing during idle time with some hosts.\
\
Kermit Data transfers will not work with Unix Raw Mode enabled. If you select Kermit from the Emulate Menu, Unix Raw Mode will become unchecked.\
\

\b Verbose Login
\b0  lets you see all of the commands during the login process.\
It is useful for troubleshooting login problems.\
\

\b FlushOutput Character = Control F
\b0 \
This is normally unchecked and uses the standard Control O if unchecked.\
Some host systems use Control O as a left arrow command.\
Setting the FlushOutput character to Control F allows Control O to be sent to the host as an arrow command.\
\
If Control F is used then the host will not receive Control F from MacWise because it will get absorbed by the Mac telnet system and be used to send a telnet ao command to the host.\
\
If Control O is used then the host will not receive Control O from MacWise because it will get absorbed by the Mac telnet system and be used to send a telnet ao command to the host.\
\
What is a telnet ao command?\
Sends the TELNET AO (Abort Output) sequence, which\
should cause the host remote system to flush all output\
from the host remote system to the user's terminal.\
\
