\b Sending a Control ] to a PICK host
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720

\f1 \cf0 Control ] is used for a Value Mark on PICK hosts.\
But that is the standard telnet escape character and causes a disconnect from the host.\
So you need to change the escape character to something else.\
Control Q is probably a safe choice if you are not using Xon/Xoff flow control.\
To change the escape character to a Control Q...\

\f2 \
If "Use the tc shell to log in" is disabled then\
The "Additional Login Options" command  should be escape ^Q\
\
If "Use the tc shell to log in" is enabled then\
The "Additional Login Options" command  should be -e ^Q\
